Mr. Ajeet Chauhan, President Human Resources -S Mobility
Ajeet Chauhan is President Human Resources and Organization Development of the Spice Global. He leads the team of seasoned HR professionals responsible for developing the Company's 10,000 + strong talent pool across i2i countries into a competitive advantage, and the quality of our workplace into a global differentiator.
 
The core focus of the HR  team is to build a “winning organization” which attracts attract, engage and retain the  “winners” in the group and make Spice "a great place to work."
 
Ajeet joined the Company in 2007, and was the Sr Vice President for the Spice Televentures from 2007 until he was appointed to his current role in July 2011.
 
Ajeet has over 18 yrs of experience of working with some of the marquee organizations like ITC, Marriott, Sheraton and the Indian Army, where he served for 7 years as a commissioned officer.
Ajeet secured his Executive MBA in HR & Marketing from IIM, Lucknow and has Bachelor degree of Science in Industrial Chemistry from Delhi University. His interests are in Music & Adventure Sports.
He can be reached at ajeet.chauhan@spiceglobal.com  
Mr. Sanjay Johri,  Head Commercial


Sanjay is currently looking after the Commercial operations. He is responsible for all the Commercial logistic activities across India.

	 

	Sanjay has over 26 years of work experience including his tenure with S Mobility Limited. Before joining S Mobility he was associated with Beta Tools where he entailed planning supply chain for their products ex factory at Italy/China, the custom clearance and internal logistics. He also holds a long and enriching service record with Indian Army where his last assignment was with  Ministry of Defense (finance), where his profile included procurement/empanelling of major equipments against Capital Expenditure of the armed forces. Also he was responsible for mapping and drawing up road map for integration of SCM for all the 3 wings of the armed forces and streamlining costs by integrating procurement and SCM activities. 

	 

	He has done an Executive Management course in Operations from XLRI, Jamshedpur and a Masters course in Materials as well as a Technical Equipment course from College of Materials Management, Jabalpur. He also holds a Diploma in SCM from Symboisis University. He is married to Ms. Veennu, an entrepreneur and they are blessed with two kids- Sanjana and Samarth. 

	 

	You can reach him at sanjay.johri@smobility.in 

	 
